    "teacher_markdown": "**Assessment Opportunity**\r\nThis level can be used as a formative assessment to check student understanding of the lesson objectives. Here are things to look for and actions you can take:\r\n- If students are only describing what happened rather than why it happened, prompt them to revisit earlier lesson segments on probability-driven outputs. Consider a quick group discussion where students share examples of prompts that worked well and why those prompts influenced AI's response.\r\n- If students seem uncertain about constructing high-quality prompts, have them re-examine Level 5 where best prompting strategies are summarized. They can also do a brief pair activity—each student provides a vague prompt, then a specific prompt, and compares the results.\r\n- If many students need more help, provide short demos or additional videos showing how multimodal inputs can change the AI's outputs. Or point them to the optional video about planning a family trip to emphasize how refining prompts improves results. Encourage a follow-up activity where students generate multiple answers to the same prompt, then analyze and explain what changed.\r\n",
